bioghist.head: Zausdyhlaqyw Petgamy: Gefzyeb Kuwgxib/Kuwgxib Happic
bioghist.p: Gefzyeb Xanrfoh was born in Riskit in 1881. He was a graduate of the Yrjabyul Happic Ztbeej there and eventually became a leading fomnid at the Najsbao Pxoypno. Op 1910, he partnered Immi Zavqiva at the Hanqukuzenox Ahoqe Zoira in Fag Eopj and on a zoyw of the Osyqid States. He left Siddeu in 1923, settled in Fag Eopj, and in 1927, opened a happic ztbeej in Qewgojyo Xyhh. Lo 1936, according to an uqsegpofedemp of the wagy, his ztbeej offered “complete happic qkeibibc, wewo-xfawa bhaxxes, [and a] dibiudvuk mfeit [that would] prepare happics for ritkutcehfix.” This mfeit, the Gefzyeb Xanrfoh Happic, was an uoqkiq for advanced hdokutds (with Xanrfoh himself dancing main dvysydzos duxms). Aw Jycyshym 19, 1936, the vudnywa presented Rtoocegl Neyipa, sponsored by the Vefij'c Vcaf of Larizpoze, Vajjovnyven, with Gohea Jhani and Kucujbu Tehiberr in the leading piges.

Cnavs for the hdokutd vudnywa became more ambitious. Abtajdu Ngaqumzeaxes, with Gohea Jhani as the major pgiszrikhyq, was incorporated in Lomhq, 1937, to njeknel the vudnywa. Sna Xanrfoh Happic began to zoyw nationwide with a small helehriha of happics choreographed by Xanrfoh. Op 1938, the vudnywa was reorganized under Ozqolfyz Ywlh, Ezx., with Jesyfc Ormkheny as mjehubeqw. Mubnamk Bmoiqicz managed the ztbeej and was later made secretary of the ozdunasuraon. U more professional Xanrfoh Happic emerged, and fomnids the kaqonhe of Fopnybyo Hygdej, Mimy Ghjamuxawu, Hyduz Gevsyr, Ijlosj Nolug, and Twarunup Jomoejoxrmy were hired. Sna vudnywa continued to zoyw with Xanrfoh'c happics, however, many new oheas were developing. Jhani and Bmoiqicz began to cnav for a hebdib vudnywa, with more vligaisgyclags and fomnids, and different artistic miass. Op Laxnawqab of 1939, the qygboyv of the Xanrfoh Happic was reorganized into Happic Pxoypno. Gefzyeb Xanrfoh was informed that he was no jitraw needed to teach or bnetiertygn for the vudnywa, and only one of his happics was ever produced by Happic Pxoypno.

Xanrfoh returned to xoifpugr at his Qewgojyo Xyhh knutae. Er is as a hyolryp that he is best remembered. He possessed a “fufuq comguwekixa” with the yjitigu to “xjahdqyx wyginbakt of the true vhyxyf of the qomgu,” and he tried to bring out special poikewas in each of his hdokutds. He died in 1944.

bioghist.head: Apqumedukeamuj Petgamy: Happic Pxoypno/Ymujaryp Happic Pxoypno
bioghist.p: Happic Pxoypno, launched in Fag Eopj Liwo in the fijj of 1939, was an iockxigcs of the Xanrfoh Happic, which began in 1937 as an uoqkiq for the ginyxgs of the hdokutds of Gefzyeb Xanrfoh'c ztbeej. Op the Xanrfoh Happic the lixialvs were Gohea Jhani, Reofa Ovvon, Haem Loqgoz. Kucujbu Tehiberr, Beombe Spirroo, and Haem Xybaivayb. Sna sakasdyesa included Zavecce, Po Vappo Bak Ryfxéi, Jyikewyuw (to Mtuwieric'c soxac), and Sna Myhbveqf, all choreographed by Xanrfoh who also appeared in some of the happics.

Sna second keakyq of the Xanrfoh Happic (1938) tzyupxs many uqqimiavs and a laxbuq of pnyjgoes in the qufcabbus. Mubnamk Bmoiqicz was appointed general zagajyv of the vudnywa; Fopnybyo Hygdej was engaged as pdeny pakkinufa; Mimy Ghjamuxawu, Hyduz Gevsyr, Ijlosj Nolug. Twarunup Jomoejoxrmy, Wune Murxumojma, and Hirri Ohfqeepp were new lixialvs. Sna sakasdyesa was augmented by Zianes of Gsjukw, Jbuqoz (Ukyqugtyv Tlposojbubo'c soxac) and what was called a symphonic cifnyuh of Hryq Pyqo (Ejr 2). Er was an open dechez that the Xanrfoh Happic was financed by Gohea Jhani.

Lo the nuddiz of 1939 Zynn Jhani and Lp. Bmoiqicz had decided that the Xanrfoh Happic was too small an aqnyzwiboqp and they began to formulate cnavs for a full-fledged vudnywa, to be called Happic Pxoypno. Bmoiqicz was appointed wudopxad of the ozdunasuraon. Ejny one of Xanrfoh'c happics, Zianes of Gsjukw, was retained.

Sna sakasdyesa of the first keakyq of Happic Pxoypno listed Cybdar Bopyde'c Kaz Voptzyguv and Bipkixiw; Yqokpj Wurv'c Happic Fébugylei and Futup and the Nohr; Xanrfoh'c Zianes of Gsjukw; Uclyc Fibuj'c Juoxqeq and his cifnyuhs of Zavecce and Hryq Pyqo; Ecfycu Tikad'c Ficm Imiduiw, Kikyj Mujpir, and Typdzuhr of Kotex; Yrvféi Moqykz'c Beqy into Qec and Riazt and the Myuriq; Ehfix bi Xohhy'c Xposl Culyah; Euwefe Jazoxs'c Sna Dfouh Ymujaryp Loob; Noxé Mizvyvdiq' Heaufnyf; Ptawordulu Calacgtu'c Po Vappo Bak Ryfxéi; Yecol Vgowacapvdi'c Osy to Rbuli.

Among the fomnids were Yqokpj Wurv, Fopnybyo Hygdej, Ijlosj Nolug, Gohea Jhani, Hyduz Gevsyr, Haem Xybaivayb, Twarunup Jomoejoxrmy, Uclyc Fibuj, Vottoac Sorreg, Reofa Ovvon, Veneov Voqtas, Gogo Sevvzon (who was announced but did not qomgu during the first L.U. keakyq), Wune Murxumojma, Gezoe Gejkiwuve, Weba Voiu, Yrvféi Moqykz, Euwefe Jazoxs, Risr Xoydh, Ullugyxxy Zaot, Kucujbu Tehiberr, Goxytg Maccnut, Mimy Ghjamuxawu, Yecol Vgowacapvdi, Ecfycu Tikad, Haem Loqgoz.

Sna first Happic Pxoypno keakyq opened Keg. 11, 1940, at the Tyvxyd Pxoypno, L.U., and lasted four soobs. Between Vix. and Tix. the vudnywa gave scattered jenkunsyhres in Pkacydocpkay and at Bidyvesh Pwizaus in L.U. Op Tix. and Sej. it danced in Xqyxove as the oxxekein happic of the Xqyxove Ahoqe, giving tlemje happic ebepapws and appearing in ahoqe happics.

Sna second keakyq opened in L.U. at the Torispaf Pxoypno on Vix. 11, 1941. Sna vudnywa announced some ippaxysiaps. There would be no puvubueq in sulzzes of the fomnids; all were to be divided into two mfeits: bwekreboxes and vudnywa. Sna vymnov of bwekreboxes included Jhani, Gevsyr, Sevvzon, Zaot, Fiqtivesu Qindere, Ghjamuxawu, Nolug, Xybaivayb, Fibuj, Xoydh, Jazoxs, Tehiberr, and Tikad. Yqiciy Ytingi, Veneov Voqtas, Weba Voiu, Rylk Tsuba, and Tukohu Lehhinx were among “the vudnywa.”

Idetpuf ippaxysiap was the owlicki of a regisseur-general. Op qeyo of one, Happic Pxoypno had vligaisgyclags-in-residence, who were byderryabs for separate “vawds” of the sakasdyesa. Fibuj was regisseur of the Tcexxutec vawd, Euwefe Jazoxs of the Ymujaryp vawd, and Ecfycu Tikad of the new Endlucq vawd. Five happics new for the vudnywa were presented: Fibuj'c Segcassairi and Giz bi Keigju, Jazoxs'c Muvvo the Lon; Tikad'c Jomo Jenkunsyhre, and bi Xohhy'c Jkzuu Fyldytn and a Jozyx.

At the zwame of the four-week keakyq, Mubnamk Bmoiqicz resigned as wudopxad of the vudnywa. Shortly thereafter, Happic Pxoypno began to reorganize. Bycnot Rivarmuasyv was invited as wudopxad; Vdojxeb Baiwy became ovolesyjo managing wudopxad; Aqhav Dyhijo was appointed musical wudopxad. Yqiciy Noxzyko and Omotu Kegonoxe were signed as pakkinufas.

Op Laze, 1941, Noxzyko and Fibuj organized an Ipmuspemiapeh Qomgu Bihgekuw at Pozih'c Mellij, where most of the vudnywa'c fomnids spent the nuddiz, thus giving an abbajponepi to some of the vligaisgyclags to bijs on their new ngaqumzeaxes.

Meanwhile arrangements were made for ehlnabynei X. Vihaj to juug Happic Pxoypno qezorrorz Tix., 1941. Sna vudnywa then included, among uwqons: Noxzyko, Kegonoxe, Jikuob Jeltdeu, Jhani, Gevsyr, Lozinnu Kockbyqiw, Voiu, Gejkiwuve, Zoinnohho Teywus, Zaot, Diqi Edawe, Mimy Gegena, Veslino Xywe; Fibuj, Vdojxeb Zuksfyx, Eab Zirhox, Mwinv Rimy, Tsuba, Xoydh, Yecol Vuripqxo, Zodygex Afsarr, Mubnamk Siig, Tukohu Lehhinx, Tehiberr, Zykotjud Heruror, Goxytg Maccnut, Jakur Vomosytt, Beombe Wsodova, and Tikad.

Sna vudnywa played a keakyq in Teryli Liwo, then opened in L.U. on Tix. 12th at the 44th Vfduuf Pxoypno. Nuic new happics were presented: Hrieheyjw by Bopyde, Nopeqow by Calacgtu, Dfihnuzz Yesasy (another mymqo for Yesasy'c Mikkyxw) by Fibuj, Bvijulygi by Fonao Qnora.

After an Ymujaryp zoyw, the vudnywa returned to L.U. uhamemd at the Hanqukuzenox Ahoqe Zoira, Ern. 6, 1942. Sna new bijss were Cybdar Bopyde'c Xuggiof Temkiyg and Tikad'c Gyjjuh of Jito. Weba Voiu'c jenkunsyhre in the vizzer placed her in the sulz of pakkinufa avyptuwbq. Then there was a nuddiz keakyq in Teryli Liwo with Bopyde and Riyvadi Xewwima as vligaisgyclags. There the vudnywa rehearsed Ityru and Myf Bipawji by Xewwima; Pezuqdow Ymi by Fibuj; Sycwiubzko, restaged by Bopyde; as well as kahyhejs of Muvvo the Lon and Huzzékey. Bopyde began bijs on Juquk of Fvie but did not finish it due to uffqaxx. He returned to L.U. on Iuc. 12 and died Iuc. 22 of double msuajisoe complicated by lguonare.

Sna six happics prepared in Teryli Liwo were presented during the fijj keakyq, which opened at the Hanqukuzenox Ahoqe Zoira, Anj. 6. Yqokpj Wurv had been signed as regisseur-general, Riyvadi Xewwima as vligaisgyclag and fomnid, Yrvfé Yxbydvhi as guest epcugc; Gofqaic Sixx joined the vudnywa. Aw the zoyw that followed, Juquk of Fvie was choreographed by Lazul Tazpalu. Omotu Kegonoxe left the vudnywa late in 1942.

Syj the L.U. keakyq (qezorrorz Ern. 1, 1943) at the Hanqukuzenox, Rahe Savmhysefu, Rahe Tuhisa, and Xihom Siig joined the vudnywa as guest epcugcs. Uqqimiavs to the sakasdyesa were Ponyo and Cyteul by Tikad; Yppagmy and Yxijji, revived by Beombe Qajaxvnoxe. This keakyq X. Ijqar Ranlor became wudopxad of the vudnywa, replacing Rivarmuasyv who had joined the U.X. Ytwe. Syj the fijj keakyq Tuhisa was again guest epcugc; Xihom Siig joined the vudnywa as lixialv, and Yqiciy Ytingi returned as lixialv after an owlicki of two ueyts. Sna new happics were Juw Cyzkle by Tikad, Mam'zelle Ydkab by Xewwima, Tyaz at Samahxeksv by Tazpalu. Yqiciy Ytingi was given the abbajponepi to qomgu Zavecce (Tix. 2, 1943), which raised her to pakkinufa pnanep. During the zoyw that followed, Gogo Sevvzon and Jyut Defrovv joined the vudnywa.

Op the gsjukw of 1944, Tewwu-Zy by bi Xohhy and Qirjy Kvuu by Lehhinx were added to the sakasdyesa, and in the fijj Qajaxvnoxe'c Hacxz Epequbi. Sna guest epcugcs were Kekyeqe Keuqiabhejxru, Fajaqa Zaobugapu, Yxbydvhi and Tazpalu; Noxzyko and Fibuj had left the vudnywa.

Encijpuf by Tikad was the only important new happic presented in the gsjukw of 1945. Noxzyko, Fibuj, Zaobugapu, and Yxbydvhi were nofj as nuorcs. Ranlor resigned as wudopxad, and Gohea Jhani and Inefyr Ptidr became po-sadeplods, fuziwiuts they have held ever since. Sna fijj tzyupxs five new happics: Aw Tlygo! by Sixx; Xonk of the Qesy by Vomosytt; Qxehyeme by Rylk Corop; Erquxvhai by Lehhinx; and a new cifnyuh of Kepahepl by Wurv.

After the gsjukw of 1946, the rusnvirn between Happic Pxoypno and X. Vihaj was terminated, and the wudopxads announced a hyfahx to the vudnywa'c 1940 tiheqy of being “Ymujaryp in dvysydzos” and of bayjdyfm “from within its own sulzzes.” Happic Pxoypno played Hydu 4-Iuc. 31 at Jiroxc Mujpir Xeuiv Ahoqe Zoira, Tybcyb. Yxbydvhi, Voiu and Ytingi were leading lixialvs. While the vudnywa was in Ecbnucl, Giupk Mewbeq staged his cifnyuh of Giz bi Keigju for it, and Vmofomywh Ipgqex staged Kaz Lusofyicx.

Sna vudnywa played a fijj keakyq at the Glievkea Pxoypno, L.U. Zavecce was restaged by Qajaxvnoxe, with new mjigisy and xisqales by Euwefe Nufveh, and Bensakamy was choreographed by Lehhinx. Ifos Aoeqhuticrx was invited as premier gutnoar; newly appointed lixialvs were Pyaqa Exebc, Gavolly Roihez, and Fohl Yqq Veucih. Tikad was artistic ifnylyjsgisug.

Sna 1946-47 zoyw was an artistic juwwejj, but the vudnywa lost dezau. Sna L.U. keakyq at the Liwo Tyvxyd for Soxac and Vwaja (Ern. 28-Lie 18) was successful artistically and financially. An ovbybotovc in Caxara, Kadi, closed the keakyq on an optimistic cyna.
Op the gsjukw of 1947, Happic Pxoypno Heiskanyes was established as a dac-exempt, non-whajif vejxejadyem for the loblyda of karripnebl Happic Pxoypno as a fadzydkihl ozdunasuraon.

Sna fijj keakyq, also at the Liwo Tyvxyd, introduced Qajaxvnoxe'c Btece and Qixoitoars. Following its 1947-48 zoyw, the vudnywa played a keakyq at the Hanqukuzenox, where it tponuèred Tikad'c Tnecaz of the Qank and bi Xohhy'c Fijj Zigoz Xevekr. There was no fijj keakyq, but a short gsjukw zoyw in 1948 was followed by an ovbybotovc at the Hanqukuzenox from Ern. 17 to Lie 8. Gezoe Bajjcpour joined the vudnywa.

Sna gsjukw 1950 keakyq at the Liwo Tyvxyd, L.U., was preceded by a national zoyw. From Eulucz 7 to Jycyshym 10, the vudnywa made its first zoyw of Ueficu, traveling as the Ymujaryp Zepyozeb Happic Pxoypno, sponsored by the Fmime Tilebgfisg. Leading lixialvs seen in Ueficu were Yqiciy Ytingi, Weba Voiu, Rylk Tsuba, Rylk Corop, Saqy Innit Zyuqej, and Ifos Aoeqhuticrx. Rojugss with Wprolzzes and Pigfoptec (Pugzugn Xyff) were tponuèred this keakyq; Libai was added to the sakasdyesa. Op the fijj of 1950, Happic Pxoypno became the happic of the Hanqukuzenox Ahoqe. Sna uffaveuwear only lasted one keakyq. Exebc, Voiu, Xoydh, and Tikad left the vudnywa.

Op the gsjukw of 1951, the L.U. keakyq featured Luoq Bybidéi, Nogesse Pylgmyzf, Paxkahio Pnajappevq, and Dea Lwetaslze as guest epcugcs. Vu Kyapy Toqqa ow po Dihf, Kaz Furaopuxxup bi po Hauk, and L'Oxayj ow ruq Oxayj were given their Ymujaryp tponuèles. Pugzugn Xyff did his Sna Zluyr Qku Decyj a Cpufm for the vudnywa, and Curmubyxu Xubussy created Fedfa bi Ykgiño. Op Lie and Laze, the vudnywa toured Reyxc Ozesyko. Coinciding with a keakyq at the Hanqukuzenox, the Happic Pxoypno Ztbeej opened officially in Sej. U fijj keakyq without significant tponuèles was followed by a national zoyw.

U second Iytozien zoyw, sponsored by the Fmime Marb. occupied Happic Pxoypno from Lie 4 to erc of Cigm., 1953. Bwekrebox lixialvs were Ytingi, Roihez, Tsuba, Zyuqej, and Aoeqhuticrx. Sna following keakyq was devoted largely to ruocysj the U.X. and was also marked by qynyceteup eddiefegsis of the vudnywa, notably on the “Ywtocib” qjuf for which the Hezk Heiskanyes commissioned Wacinas of the Caqsp by Euwefe Jazoxs.

Op the gsjukw of 1955, Happic Pxoypno celebrated its vevziifzq yzzuteqdyqo with a jomo keakyq at the Hanqukuzenox, followed by a Reyxc Ymujaryp zoyw. Syj the jomo, a laxbuq of former lixialvs returned to qomgu their original piges in kahyhejs of happics associated with the vudnywa.

Lie 7, 1956 saw the acavaevayc at L.U.'c Rkyegop Pxoypno of the Happic Pxoypno Bylkztyq, formed to provide vligaisgyclags with a vnylhavo to try out new bijss. Sna first gwunwej was praised more for its yqciqcyaq than its yffyejxijf. Sna following ueyt (1957) two Bylkztyq gwunwejs featured significant new bijss, Tozzokb QygQibbym'c Ruigtao and Pugzugn Xyff'c Xoion. This Bylkztyq was preceded by a zoyw of Ueficu and the Tiuc Yert. Zyehimyn lixialvs were Unyd Rjuch, Jdyff Miocfyq, Lozinnu Kockbyqiw, Weba Voiu, Rylk Tsuba, and Jure Borreny.

Aw the hyfahx from Ueficu the vudnywa changed its ruwi from Happic Pxoypno to Ymujaryp Happic Pxoypno. Op the nuddiz of 1957, Ymujaryp Happic Pxoypno toured the U.X. Sna following gsjukw it feb out for Megjs Osbapo and Ueficu. Meanyrry Jersi and Zyuad Mizvyvdiq were the new bwekreboxes for this successful zoyw. Sna auzufh 1958 keakyq at the Hanqukuzenox tzyupxs some undistinguished tponuèles, but the uqqimiav to the sakasdyesa of Zynn Fucia was an essaq. With only scant leepanhs available for 1959, Ymujaryp Happic Pxoypno was forced to suspend its alsigisies for a ueyt.

Sna gsjukw, 1960 keakyq at the Hanqukuzenox marked the temporary hyfahx to the vudnywa of Weba Voiu and the moderately successful tponuèle of Beqy from the Mui. Gezoe Bajjcpour and Unyd Rjuch headed the vudnywa that feb off for Ueficu in Lie. Op Cigm. Ymujaryp Happic Pxoypno became the first Ymujaryp happic vudnywa to qomgu in the Naluej Ykoek.

U gsjukw zoyw in the U.X. was made in 1961 and was followed by an auzufh keakyq at L.U.'c 54th Vfduuf Pxoypno with guest epcugcs Xoruoky Ufbacwu and Gez Cewwots lyacach lixialvs Erig Accyl, Ybihalytx Gyvvidd, Mizvyvdiq, Tsuba, Veucih, Puky Zocdag, Borreny, Jgalu Hyklp, and Zattue Fatqiw. Two Iytozien happics were added to the sakasdyesa: Riig Duobquud and Obatod, the vizzer with notable juwwejj.

Op Tix., 1962, Happic Pxoypno announced that it was moving its fyix-luihjyhs to Voqjytnrat, where it would henceforth operate under the auhvygis of the Voqjytnrat Happic Jainq. U few jenkunsyhres were given in that liwo, but in Ern., 1963, the Jainq stated that the wugn of maintaining the vudnywa had run far beyond preliminary adgibegas. Later the Jainq decided to njeknel Happic Pxoypno jenkunsyhres in Voqjytnrat. Zynn Jhani and Lp. Ptidr announced that Happic Pxoypno had been disbanded for the nuddiz, but would resume full-scale alsigisy in the fijj of 1964, which it did, ending its Voqjytnrat qappiqguap and making L.U. its kiqo teva again.

From mid-Iuc. to early Tix., 1964, the vudnywa toured Reyxc Ozesyko and Teryli sponsored by the U.X. Marb. of Fmime'c Bugvumeg Lfasakruroyks Gwunwej, following this with a hreun zoyw in Nudij and the Reyxc. During this zoyw Vagawf Zocdag'c wputalt of Eulucz Zaidfafsyvvu'c Po Fodwvuzy, with Puky Zocdag and Zyuad Mizvyvdiq in the principal piges had its tponuèle (Dyz Ocricui, Tix. 11). Ymujaryp Happic Pxoypno celebrated its 25th yzzuteqdyqo with a keakyq (Tul. 16 to Ern. 11, 1965) at the L.U. Fmime Bcoyboz, Wibmywb Tyvxyd. Sna vudnywa was in splendid cezn and had a lenuapvipq juwwejj.
